SUMMARY:GTApreneurs April 8-2026 Downtown Toronto Business Networking Even
 t
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Women in Business Networking Group (TWIB)\nJoin us for
  a vibrant Business Networking Event in Toronto where you may meet your ne
 xt client\, referral partner or friend. Discover opportunities and connect
 ! Register now.\n\n**REGISTER HERE:** https://gtapreneurs.com/networking-e
 vents-toronto\n\n**Venue:** Firkin on Yonge\n**Address:** 207 Yonge St\, T
 oronto\, ON ***(Across from CF Eaton Centre)***\n**Transit:** Get off at Q
 ueen subway station\n**Parking:** Paid parking under Eaton Centre\n\nThis 
 is a casual event with no set structure. When you get to the pub\, head up
 stairs to the 2nd floor (Elevator or stairs) to meet us. We’ll check you
  in\, give you a nametag and an ice breaker card\, and introduce you to th
 e others.\n\n\\*APPETIZERS will be PROVIDED\\*\nPlease purchase a beverage
  and/or a meal to support the venue.\n\n**TICKETS:**\n**GTApreneurs' Refer
 ral Group\, Exhibitor and Mega Networking Members:** Free\n**Non-members:*
 * $20\n***\\*Includes a Guest Contact Sheet*** emailed to you the day afte
 r the event. Note: You need to attend the event to receive the sheet.\n\n*
 *HOSTS:**\n**Tammy Defoe\,** President of GTApreneurs\nLearn more about Ta
 mmy's Coaching services at [www.gtapreneurs.com/business-coaching-toronto]
 (www.gtapreneurs.com/business-coaching-toronto)\n\n**QUESTIONS ABOUT THE E
 VENT?** Call 416 522-7770 or email info@gtapreneurs.com\n\nand\n\n**Gaby A
 bdelgadir\,** 5-time Int'l Best-Selling Author\, Entrepreneur\, Life Coach
  and a Motivational Speaker.\n\nGaby is a Jack Canfield Certified Success 
 Principles Trainer\, Certified Linn Method Clutter Cleaning Coach & Feng S
 ui Practitioner. Passionate about Mental Wellness\, Gaby is also a Certifi
 ed Mental Wellness in the Workplace Leadership. Another topic close to Gab
 y's heart is anti-bullying and anti-discrimination - something she has gon
 e through herself. In her Award-Winning Book "The Book on Discrimination -
  Real Life Stories of Struggles and Triumphs" - available in Amazon both i
 n English and Spanish\, she has interviewed kids from Grade 6 and above an
 d people in the workplace who have gone through similar experiences. Other
 s also have shared their discrimination stories in her book. She now speak
 s in schools and community centers.\n\nGaby has been studying Personal Gro
 wth and Leadership for over 20 years and for the last 8 years\, she has fo
 cused more on spirituality. She loves to travel\, read good books and help
  people in need.\n\n**CONTACT GABY:** [www.totaldeclutter.com](www.totalde
 clutter.com) \\| [www.gabyabdelgadir.com](www.gabyabdelgadir.com) \\| [www
 .youtube.com/@gabyabdelgadir844](www.youtube.com/@gabyabdelgadir844) \\| L
 inkedIn: [www.tinyurl.com/5dfyu28v](www.tinyurl.com/5dfyu28v) \\| 416\\-66
 9\\-2057\n\nView all of GTApreneurs events and services at www.gtapreneurs
 .com\n\nWe look forward to seeing you there!
